step-four-add-a-demo-dependency.html.body:
Step Four:  Add a Demo DependencyOf course, no component repository is complete without a demo.  We often want to show how our component will coexist and interact with other libraries and components.  In this case, I would like to demonstrate how one can use the library to create overlays in OpenSeadragon (OSD).The first thing we want to do is add an example dependency in gulpfile.config.js just underneath where we added our required dependencies (i.e. base-component and paper.js).  We need the entire directory for this one, not just the minified file, so we will create a path to the whole build directory:// libs that MAY be included in a consuming app but are used here for examples purposes 
this.examplesDeps = [
     'node_modules/openseadragon/build/**/*'
];
Then we will add the following line to our index.html head:
Now, we just need to add some markup to our example index.html to get OSD working in the demo.  Put this in the : 
    .openseadragon { 
        width: 800px; height: 600px; border: 1px solid black; color: #333; background-color: black; 
    } 

And put this in the :


    var viewer = OpenSeadragon({ 
            id: "osd", 
            prefixUrl: "/js/openseadragon/images/", 
            tileSources: [{ 
                "@context": "http://iiif.io/api/image/2/context.json", 
                "@id": "http://libimages.princeton.edu/loris2/pudl0001%2F4609321%2Fs42%2F00000002.jp2", 
                "height": 7200, 
                "width": 5093, 
                "profile": 
                    [ "http://iiif.io/api/image/2/level2.json" ], 
                    "protocol": "http://iiif.io/api/image", 
                    "tiles": [{ "scaleFactors": [ 1, 2, 4, 8, 16, 32 ], 
                    "width": 1024 }] 
            }] 
        });

    // add our  element as an OSD overlay...
    var element = document.getElementById('myCanvas');
    var rect = new OpenSeadragon.Rect(0, 0, 1, viewer.viewport.getAspectRatio());

    viewer.addOverlay({
     element: element,
     location: rect
    });


Reload your demo page, and you should see the overlay (you may want to make the line color red so it's easier to see).
